# PART 5 — ARCHITECTURE REFERENCE

## Stack
- Frontend: Vanilla JS (no framework) — app.js, editor.js, explorer.js, ui.js, etc.
- Backend: Netlify Functions (Node.js serverless)
- Database: Neon (PostgreSQL + pgvector)
- AI Gateway: kaixu67.skyesoverlondon.workers.dev (Cloudflare Worker)
- AI Model: Gemini via Kaixu gateway (kAIxU injects KAIXU_CANON on every generate/stream call)
- Billing: Stripe
- Email: SendGrid
- Auth: JWT (HS256) + TOTP MFA + bcrypt
- Vector search: pgvector (768-dim, Gemini text-embedding-004)

## Gateway call pattern (ALL AI calls must follow this)
```
fetch(`${KAIXU_GATE_BASE}/v1/generate`, {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Authorization': `Bearer ${KAIXU_GATE_TOKEN}`,
    'Content-Type': 'application/json'
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    model: 'gemini-2.5-flash',     // optional, gate default is fine
    system: 'Your instructions',   // optional, additive (KAIXU_CANON already injected)
    messages: [...],               // conversation history
    output: { format: 'json' },    // optional
    generationConfig: { ... }      // optional
  })
})
// Response: { ok, text, model, finishReason, usage }
```

## Embeddings call pattern
```
fetch(`${KAIXU_GATE_BASE}/v1/embeddings`, {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { 'Authorization': `Bearer ${KAIXU_GATE_TOKEN}`, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    content: ['string or array of strings'],
    taskType: 'RETRIEVAL_DOCUMENT' // or RETRIEVAL_QUERY for search
  })
})
// Response: { ok, embeddings: [{ index, values: float[768] }] }
```

## Key rules — never break these
- NEVER call Gemini, OpenAI, or any AI provider directly from Netlify functions
- NEVER put API keys in client-side code or git commits
- NEVER send KAIXU_CANON in your system field (gate injects it)
- NEVER send safetySettings (gate strips them)
- ALWAYS use Authorization: Bearer for gateway calls
- ALWAYS check data.ok before reading data.text

